                <p><label type="entry">VOURLA</label>, a sea port of Asia Minor, on the site of the
                    ancient Clazomene, one of the twelve great cities of Ionia. It is built on two
                    eminences; and one division is inhabited by Christians, who occupy about 500
                    houses, and possess two churches; the remainder of the town is inhabited by
                    Turks. It is now of little importance. Vourla is twenty-five miles west of
                    Smyrna.</p>
            </div>
